Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, Lisa Monaco, spoke with President Hadi of Yemen to commend the efforts of the new government in implementing peace agreements and recommendations. Monaco emphasized the United States' commitment to supporting Yemen's political transition process. They discussed Yemen's progress in drafting a new constitution, preparing for a referendum, and electing a new government. Both Monaco and President Hadi highlighted the importance of all communities in ensuring peace, stability, governance, and security in Yemen. They also reaffirmed the partnership between the United States and Yemen in countering the threat from al-Qa'ida in the Arabian Peninsula.